HEADWORD: civil rights
<hw>civil rights</hw></mhw> <def>a legal
right or rights belonging to a person by reason of citizenship,
including especially the fundamental freedoms and privileges guaranteed
by the 13th and 14th amendments and subsequent acts of congress,
including the right to legal and social and economic equality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

